The following script is provided as practical example. It implements a loop connecting channel pairs in a loop (b1->c1, b2->c2, b3->c3)

Edit networks.xml adding the NETCONF access parameters for your device.

Usage:

python3 switch-loop-netconf.py --config=networks.xml --loops=10 | grep '^#'


Output:


This same procedure and values are used in the example part of the userguide for the device directly using GPIB.

Corresponding GPIB script with identical functionality is also provided - switch-loop-gpib.py:

Usage:

sudo python3 switch-loop-gpib.py  | grep '^#'
